.TH "CXKCDPASS" "1" "May 12, 2022" "cxkcdpass 0.0.1" "cxkcdpass"
.hy
.SH NAME
.PP
cxkcdpass - generate random passphrases from wordlist(s)
.SH SYNOPSIS
.PP
\f[B]cxkcdpass\f[R] [\f[I]OPTION\f[R]\&...]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
A password generator which generates strong passphrases from wordlists,
inspired by XKCD 936 (https://xkcd.com/936/).
Based on xkcdpass (https://github.com/redacted/XKCD-password-generator),
a Python implementation, whereas \f[V]cxkcdpass\f[R] is implemented in
\f[V]C\f[R], therefore the c in cxkcdpass.
.IP
.nf
\f[C]
$ cxkcdpass
> coroner nutlike sandbank remarry judge yesterday
\f[R]
.fi
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\f[B]-h\f[R], \f[B]\[en]help\f[R]
Print help and exit
.TP
\f[B]-V\f[R], \f[B]\[en]version\f[R]
Print version and exit
.TP
\f[B]-w\f[R] \f[I]WORDFILE\f[R], \f[B]\[en]wordfile\f[R]=\f[I]WORDFILE\f[R]
Specify that the file \f[I]WORDFILE\f[R] contains the list of valid
words from which to generate passphrases.
Multiple wordfiles can be provided.
Provided wordfiles: \f[V]eff-long\f[R], \f[V]eff-short\f[R],
\f[V]eff-special\f[R], \f[V]legacy\f[R], \f[V]spa-mich\f[R] (Spanish),
\f[V]fin-kotus\f[R] (Finnish), \f[V]fr-freelang\f[R] (French),
\f[V]fr-corrected.txt\f[R] (French), \f[V]pt-ipublicis\f[R]
(Portuguese), \f[V]ita-wiki\f[R] (Italian), \f[V]ger-anlx\f[R] (German),
\f[V]eff_large_de_sample.wordlist\f[R] (German), \f[V]nor-nb\f[R]
(Norwegian) (default=\f[V]eff-long\f[R])
.TP
\f[B]-m\f[R], \f[B]\[en]min\f[R]=\f[I]MIN_LENGTH\f[R]
Generate passphrases containing words with at least \f[I]MIN_LENGTH\f[R]
characters.
.TP
\f[B]-M\f[R], \f[B]\[en]max\f[R]=\f[I]MAX_LENGTH\f[R]
Generate passphrases containing words with at most \f[I]MAX_LENGTH\f[R]
characters.
.TP
\f[B]-n\f[R], \f[B]\[en]num-words\f[R]=\f[I]NUM_WORDS\f[R]
Generate passphrases containing exactly \f[I]NUM_WORDS\f[R] words.
.TP
\f[B]-r\f[R], \f[B]\[en]regex-match\f[R]=\f[I]REGEX\f[R]
Limit passphrases to only include words matching the regex pattern
\f[I]REGEX\f[R] (e.g.\ \f[V]\[aq]\[rs]\[ha][a-z]*$\[aq]\f[R]).
.TP
\f[B]-v\f[R], \f[B]\[en]verbose\f[R]
Report various metrics for given options and general verbose output.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
\f[B]cxkcdpass\f[R]
Prints a random passphrase
.TP
\f[B]cxkcdpass -w ./my-list-of-words.txt\f[R]
Prints a random passphrase based on words in ./my-list-of-words.txt
.TP
\f[B]cxkcdpass -n 10\f[R]
Prints a random passphrase with 10 words
